content.description:
This climbs the top half of

Valhalla

, starting on the flake halfway up the boulder.
content.protection: A pad and spotter for the boulder behind you.

content.description: Although perhaps a little contrived, this problem is extremely enjoyable and has lots of cool movement. Start down low on two obvious underclings on the left side of the boulder. Using a few good crimps, go up and right to a sharp crimp rail. Then go up to a sloper and make a committing move up and left to the jug. The left arete is off. This is a really fun problem!
content.protection: A pad or two. A spotter is nice for the last move to protect against a slam into the rock behind.
content.location:
This is on the Incuts Overhang, on the same boulder as

Deeper Cuts

near to

The Pillar

(V2) and just uphill from Nook's Rock.

content.description: On the Incuts Boulder, start on the very bottom right side. Go left to the big chalked holds in the middle of the rock and then make a big move to the jug on the left arete. Then adjust feet, throw for the top jug, and top out to the right.
content.location:
On the Incuts Boulder, this is just below the

Slot Overhang

and SW of

The Pillar

. Start down in the right corner.

content.description: On the Incuts Boulder, start at about chest height on the left arete and cruise on up the arete to the big jug. Top out left.
content.location:
On the Incuts Boulder, this is just below the

Slot Overhang

and SW of

The Pillar

. It is just a short walk downhill (north) from the Cloud Shadow's backside.

content.description: This is on the left arete of the Incuts Boulder. Start on two obvious low jugs; one an underbanger and the other a decent sidepull. Slap up the arete and use some small holds get to the jug halfway up. Then go up to the top jug and mantle over the left side. Awesome problem! Powerful moves on good holds.
content.location:
On the left side of Incuts Boulder, this is located just below the

Slot Overhang

and SW of

The Pillar

(V2).
